# AI Agent Rules — Library Management System

## Hard constraints (never violate)
- NEVER write a concrete repository or strategy class without first defining its interface as an abc.ABC.
- ALWAYS practice TDD: write the failing test first, then the implementation.
- NEVER use external databases, network calls, file I/O, or third-party APIs. All storage is in-memory.
- Inject all dependencies through constructors (Dependency Injection). Never instantiate dependencies inside a class.

## Quality targets
- Branch coverage >= 85% (assignment minimum is 70%).
- 200+ unit and integration tests.
- 0 bugs, 0 vulnerabilities, Maintainability rating A or B.

## Design
- Layers: models (entities) -> storage (ABC repositories + in-memory impl) -> services (business logic).
- Apply SOLID. Functions must be small, typed, documented, duplication-free.
- Required GoF patterns: Strategy (fine calculation), Observer (book availability notification).
